              Then <m>(ğ‘‹, ğ’¯)</m> and <m>(ğ‘‹, ğ’¯â€²)</m> are different topological spaces if <m>ğ’¯ â‰  ğ’¯â€²</m>, even though the underlying set <m>ğ‘‹</m> is the same.
            </p>
